<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>emsenn.net</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/texts/</link><description>Recent content on emsenn.net</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Wed, 04 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/texts/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>The Interactive Semioverse</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/texts/interactive-semioverse/</link><pubDate>Wed, 04 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/texts/interactive-semioverse/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="the-interactive-semioverse"&gt;The Interactive Semioverse&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id="abstract"&gt;Abstract&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;ll construct an &lt;strong&gt;Interactive Semioverse&lt;/strong&gt;: a mathematical environment in which we work with &lt;strong&gt;things&lt;/strong&gt; only through &lt;strong&gt;semiotic interaction&lt;/strong&gt;, and where all induced semantic material lives inside a disciplined closure system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Concretely, the Semioverse includes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a semantic field &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; that is a &lt;strong&gt;complete Heyting algebra&lt;/strong&gt;, equipped with
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a join-continuous &lt;strong&gt;modal closure&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;j&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;j:H\to H&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, and&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a join-continuous &lt;strong&gt;Heyting–comonadic temporal trace&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;G&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;G:H\to H&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a finitary &lt;strong&gt;operator algebra&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="sans-serif"&gt;O&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="sans-serif"&gt;p&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;d&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;e&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;\mathsf{Op}^{\mathrm{def}}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; generated by a typed &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;λ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;\lambda&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;-calculus and interpreted as semantic endomorphisms &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;n&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H^n\to H&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a system of &lt;strong&gt;fragments&lt;/strong&gt;, i.e. finitely generated modal–temporal Heyting subalgebras of &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;three closure mechanisms—semantic, syntactic (with finitary justification), and fusion—whose composite &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="script"&gt;S&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;\mathcal{S}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; has a least fixed point.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On top of that core, I introduce a thing-facing layer:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Core Semiotic Universe</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/texts/core-semiotic-universe/</link><pubDate>Wed, 31 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/texts/core-semiotic-universe/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href="../index.md" class="link-internal"&gt;interactive semioverse&lt;/a&gt; extends a &lt;a href="../../semiotic-universe/semiotic-universe.md" class="link-internal"&gt;semiotic universe&lt;/a&gt; — a self-sustaining &lt;a href="../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/sign.md" class="link-internal"&gt;sign&lt;/a&gt; system in which everything sayable is meaningful and everything meaningful is sayable. The base layer provides:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a meaning domain &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; that is a complete &lt;a href="../../../../concepts/heyting-algebra/index.md" class="link-internal"&gt;Heyting algebra&lt;/a&gt; (intuitionistic, because not every question about a &lt;a href="../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/sign.md" class="link-internal"&gt;sign&lt;/a&gt;&amp;rsquo;s meaning resolves to yes or no),&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a modal &lt;a href="../../../../concepts/closure-operator/index.md" class="link-internal"&gt;closure operator&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;j&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;j&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; formalizing &lt;a href="../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/habit.md" class="link-internal"&gt;habit&lt;/a&gt;-formation,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a &lt;a href="../../semiotic-universe/terms/trace-comonad.md" class="link-internal"&gt;trace comonad&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;G&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;G&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; formalizing semiotic provenance — the &lt;a href="../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/sign.md" class="link-internal"&gt;sign&lt;/a&gt; chains that produced each meaning,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;definable operators interpreted into &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; (the grammar of the sign system),&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;fragments (bounded interpretive contexts) and a composite &lt;a href="../../../../concepts/closure-operator/index.md" class="link-internal"&gt;closure operator&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="script"&gt;S&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;\mathcal{S}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This layer ensures that all semantic work is closed under logic, &lt;a href="../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/habit.md" class="link-internal"&gt;habit&lt;/a&gt;-formation, and semiotic provenance before any handle-facing interaction is added.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Footprints, Delta, and Subtraction</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/texts/footprints-delta-subtraction/</link><pubDate>Wed, 31 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/texts/footprints-delta-subtraction/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;With &lt;a href="../terms/interaction-surface.md" class="link-internal"&gt;interaction surfaces&lt;/a&gt; in place, we can define how a handle affects the meaning domain and how to compare or remove that influence. These three operations formalize the pragmatic dimension of &lt;a href="../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/semiosis.md" class="link-internal"&gt;semiosis&lt;/a&gt;: meanings have consequences (footprints), those consequences can be compared (delta), and influence can be disciplinedly removed (subtraction).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="footprint"&gt;Footprint&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href="../terms/footprint.md" class="link-internal"&gt;footprint&lt;/a&gt; of a handle is the closure of its &lt;a href="../terms/handle-fragment.md" class="link-internal"&gt;handle fragment&lt;/a&gt; under the state&amp;rsquo;s operators — the total meaning the handle acquires through all its &lt;a href="../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/index.md" class="link-internal"&gt;semiotic&lt;/a&gt; encounters. As a physical footprint &lt;a href="../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/index-sign.md" class="link-internal"&gt;indexes&lt;/a&gt; the passage of a body, the semiotic footprint indexes the passage of a handle through the sign system.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Handles and Interactions</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/texts/handles-interactions/</link><pubDate>Wed, 31 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/texts/handles-interactions/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href="../index.md" class="link-internal"&gt;interactive semioverse&lt;/a&gt; introduces handles as &lt;a href="../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/index-sign.md" class="link-internal"&gt;indexical&lt;/a&gt; references and defines a calculus of interactions that generate semantic material — formalizing how &lt;a href="../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/sign.md" class="link-internal"&gt;signs&lt;/a&gt; engage with what lies outside the sign system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="handles"&gt;Handles&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;a href="../terms/handle.md" class="link-internal"&gt;handle&lt;/a&gt; is a persistent &lt;a href="../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/index-sign.md" class="link-internal"&gt;indexical&lt;/a&gt; reference to a thing. It is not itself an element of the meaning domain &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;; it is an external pointer mapped into &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; by a seed function &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;η&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;\eta&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. This formalizes Peirce&amp;rsquo;s &lt;a href="../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/index-sign.md" class="link-internal"&gt;index&lt;/a&gt;: a &lt;a href="../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/sign.md" class="link-internal"&gt;sign&lt;/a&gt; connected to its object by existential relation rather than convention or resemblance.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Semantic and Semiotic Context</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/texts/semantic-semiotic-context/</link><pubDate>Wed, 31 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/texts/semantic-semiotic-context/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;The interactive semioverse draws on both semantic and &lt;a href="../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/index.md" class="link-internal"&gt;semiotic&lt;/a&gt; traditions, specifically those that align with a relational ontology — where relations are prior to entities. The mathematical structures correspond to concepts in &lt;a href="../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/schools/peircean-semiotics.md" class="link-internal"&gt;Peircean&lt;/a&gt; semiotics: indexicality, habit, unlimited semiosis, and the pragmatic maxim.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="semantics"&gt;Semantics&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Heyting algebra &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; provides the semantic domain — a constructive logic of meanings. The implication &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;a&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;⇒&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;b&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;a \Rightarrow b&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; captures constructive entailment; the modal closure &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;j&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;j&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; formalizes &lt;a href="../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/habit.md" class="link-internal"&gt;habit&lt;/a&gt;-formation; the trace &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;G&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;G&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; formalizes semiotic provenance. These are the semantic structures that the interactive layer operates on.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>